[red-db-1.0]
Initial Release
[red-db-1.1]
Fixed server socket time-out that caused system abort every two hours.
Fixed client socket time-out that caused client to abort.
Fixed server abort due to syntax error involving asterisk.
Fixed outfile so that numeric (non-text) values are not enclosed in quotation marks.
Merged 'tcp' and 'sndrcv' libraries into library 'comm' to stream-line the communication library. 
Minor stream-lining of virtual machine (vm) library.
Minor changes to server (srv) to accomodate new 'comm' library.
Minor changes to client (cli) to accomodate new 'comm' library.
[red-db-1.2]
Fixed server race when column defined with auto_increment.
Fixed null value translation. Null values did not translate unless enclosed in quotes.
Finished support for DATE, DATETIME and TIMESTAMP column types.
[red-db-1.3]
Fixed issue where combination of USING and ON conditions returned empty result.
[red-db-1.4]
Increased number of column names in USING clause.
[red-db-1.5]
Fixed server where null values were saved incorrectly.
[red-db-1.6]
Fixed server where plain-text password was being prepended to hashed password.
